# Finance laws (absolute)

- ALL monetary values are **integers in Toman**. No float, no Decimal, ever.
- Price is snapshotted onto the Enrollment at creation. NEVER read a Course's live
  `current_price` for an existing enrollment.
- Once an Invoice is issued, the enrollment's money fields are frozen.
- Invoice.total_amount = enrollment.final_amount (frozen copy at issue).
- Invariant, validated on create/update:
  `sum(installments.amount where status != 'cancelled') == invoice.total_amount`.
- Installment & Invoice statuses are ALWAYS **derived** from payments — never set by hand:
  - installment `paid` when sum(payments) >= amount;
    `partially_paid` when 0 < sum < amount;
    `overdue` when past due_date and not fully paid;
    `cancelled` only via the drop flow.
  - invoice `paid` when all non-cancelled installments paid;
    `partially_paid` when any payment exists; `void` when enrollment dropped with no payments.
- On enrollment → `dropped`: pending / partially_paid installments → `cancelled`.
  Refunds of money already received are OUT OF SCOPE (record a note only; no refund ledger).
- Every payment records `recorded_by` (the staff user) and writes an Activity via `log_activity`.
